GUARDIAN LIFE INSURANCE COMPANY OF AMERICA v. Harry KORTZ (two cases). Nos. 3366, 3367. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Sept. 16, 1946. Lowell White, of Denver, Colo., for appellant. Samuel S. Ginsberg and Max P. Zall, both of Denver, Colo., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, HUXMAN, and MURRAH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on motion of appellant.
